5:
You want the Vesta to ally with the
Guild Knights?
8:
Allies, teammates, hired blades...
whatever you want to call it. I'm
saying we could use your help.
10:
We'd be much tougher in a fight if
we had you folk as backup!
18:
Ehh... We kind of do, and we kind of
don't.
24:
You'd be a big help for us out in the
field, since, like I'm always saying,
the Guild Knights are always
woefully understaffed.
27:
That said, there's also the concern
that a peacekeeping force like us
shouldn't need that much firepower
at our disposal.
31:
...So we could be utilized in combat
against other people.
33: I do not wish for that.
37:
Neither do I. However, it is a
possibility.
40:
If the worst comes to pass, it will be
difficult to extricate yourself once
you are allied. You should take care
in making your decision.
42:
Spend some time mulling over your
options before you choose.
45:
Well, yeah. Take the day to think it
over. And you've got people you can
talk to now, don't you?
55:
And that's why I need your help,
Hero of the Red Soup.
61:
I... don't know if someone like me
could help you make a decision like
that.
65: I will not tolerate such a claim.
70:
What? I haven't even said anything
yet.
73:
You are the hero I've acknowledged.
Therefore, your opinions hold weight.
State them with confidence.
75:
I know I can rely on you—you are a
good man. Strong, wise, gentle,
pleasant to the senses—
83:
Pleasant to the what now? Are you
messing with me?!
94: In any case... Let's think it over.
101:
First of all, how do you generally feel
about working alongside the Guild
Knights?
104:
It seems like a good prospect.
Protecting that city would help
secure a future for the Vesta.
108:
But there are people that want to
use the Guild Knights for their own
agendas. Zekhel and Dul Kugala
were warning you about that.
112:
The Vesta will not submit to
deceitful masters. It would be foolish
of us to repeat the same mistakes.
114:
Moreover, it is concerning that I
don't know who those people are...
117: I have made up my mind.
137:
Your words have taken root within
me, and I have grown thanks to you.
139:
Put another way, you have already
done more than enough for me.
170:
But, are you sure about this? The
higher-ups will surely take notice of
you.
178:
I believe the captain told you to
keep a low profile, correct?
181:
I am a warrior, as well as the Archon
of the Spirit Horns.
184:
If anyone intends to take advantage
of the Vesta, their Oudo will expose
them.
187:
I see. So you're operating
undercover.
197:
After all, I'm following in the
footsteps of a certain hero.
203:
Huh? Hero? Hold on, tell me more
about that!
